              <DefinitionShort>pertaining to being to the left of some point of reference</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>left</Gloss>
                <Gloss>left side</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In {S:04700600700030} the phrase ὅπλον ἀριστερόν, literally ‘left-hand weapon,’ refers to a weapon used by the left hand and therefore a defensive weapon, while ὅπλον δεξιόν, literally ‘weapon for the right hand,’ refers to an offensive weapon.|For an interpretation of ἀριστερός as part of an idiom in {S:04101003700030}, see {D:87.35}.</Comments>
